name: Go 1 and the Future of Go Programs
zip
description: Package tar implements access to tar archives.

name: bufio
description: Package zip provides support for reading and writing ZIP archives.

name: builtin
description: Package bufio implements buffered I/O. It wraps an io.Reader or io.Writer object, creating another object (Reader or Writer) that also implements the interface but provides buffering and some help for textual I/O.

name: bytes
description: Package builtin provides documentation for Go's predeclared identifiers.

name: compress
description: Package bytes implements functions for the manipulation of byte slices.

name: flate
description: Package bzip2 implements bzip2 decompression.

name: gzip
description: Package flate implements the DEFLATE compressed data format, described in RFC 1951.

name: lzw
description: Package gzip implements reading and writing of gzip format compressed files, as specified in RFC 1952.

name: zlib
description: Package lzw implements the Lempel-Ziv-Welch compressed data format, described in T. A. Welch, “A Technique for High-Performance Data Compression”, Computer, 17(6) (June 1984), pp 8-19.

name: container
description: Package zlib implements reading and writing of zlib format compressed data, as specified in RFC 1950.

name: list
description: Package heap provides heap operations for any type that implements heap.Interface.

name: ring
description: Package list implements a doubly linked list.

name: context
description: Package ring implements operations on circular lists.

name: crypto
description: Package context defines the Context type, which carries deadlines, cancellation signals, and other request-scoped values across API boundaries and between processes.

name: aes
description: Package crypto collects common cryptographic constants.

name: cipher
description: Package aes implements AES encryption (formerly Rijndael), as defined in U.S. Federal Information Processing Standards Publication 197.

name: des
description: Package cipher implements standard block cipher modes that can be wrapped around low-level block cipher implementations.

name: dsa
description: Package des implements the Data Encryption Standard (DES) and the Triple Data Encryption Algorithm (TDEA) as defined in U.S. Federal Information Processing Standards Publication 46-3.

name: ecdsa
description: Package dsa implements the Digital Signature Algorithm, as defined in FIPS 186-3.

name: ed25519
description: Package ecdsa implements the Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm, as defined in FIPS 186-3.

name: elliptic
description: Package ed25519 implements the Ed25519 signature algorithm.

name: hmac
description: Package elliptic implements several standard elliptic curves over prime fields.

name: md5
description: Package hmac implements the Keyed-Hash Message Authentication Code (HMAC) as defined in U.S. Federal Information Processing Standards Publication 198.

name: rand
description: Package md5 implements the MD5 hash algorithm as defined in RFC 1321.

name: rc4
description: Package rand implements a cryptographically secure random number generator.

name: rsa
description: Package rc4 implements RC4 encryption, as defined in Bruce Schneier's Applied Cryptography.

name: sha1
description: Package rsa implements RSA encryption as specified in PKCS#1.

name: sha256
description: Package sha1 implements the SHA-1 hash algorithm as defined in RFC 3174.

name: sha512
description: Package sha256 implements the SHA224 and SHA256 hash algorithms as defined in FIPS 180-4.

name: subtle
description: Package sha512 implements the SHA-384, SHA-512, SHA-512/224, and SHA-512/256 hash algorithms as defined in FIPS 180-4.

name: tls
description: Package subtle implements functions that are often useful in cryptographic code but require careful thought to use correctly.

name: x509
description: Package tls partially implements TLS 1.2, as specified in RFC 5246, and TLS 1.3, as specified in RFC 8446.

name: pkix
description: Package x509 parses X.509-encoded keys and certificates.

name: database
description: Package pkix contains shared, low level structures used for ASN.1 parsing and serialization of X.509 certificates, CRL and OCSP.

name: driver
description: Package sql provides a generic interface around SQL (or SQL-like) databases.

name: debug
description: Package driver defines interfaces to be implemented by database drivers as used by package sql.

name: elf
description: Package dwarf provides access to DWARF debugging information loaded from executable files, as defined in the DWARF 2.0 Standard at http://dwarfstd.org/doc/dwarf-2.0.0.pdf

name: gosym
description: Package elf implements access to ELF object files.

name: macho
description: Package gosym implements access to the Go symbol and line number tables embedded in Go binaries generated by the gc compilers.

name: pe
description: Package macho implements access to Mach-O object files.

name: plan9obj
description: Package pe implements access to PE (Microsoft Windows Portable Executable) files.

name: encoding
description: Package plan9obj implements access to Plan 9 a.out object files.

name: ascii85
description: Package encoding defines interfaces shared by other packages that convert data to and from byte-level and textual representations.

name: asn1
description: Package ascii85 implements the ascii85 data encoding as used in the btoa tool and Adobe's PostScript and PDF document formats.

name: base32
description: Package asn1 implements parsing of DER-encoded ASN.1 data structures, as defined in ITU-T Rec X.690.

name: base64
description: Package base32 implements base32 encoding as specified by RFC 4648.

name: binary
description: Package base64 implements base64 encoding as specified by RFC 4648.

name: csv
description: Package binary implements simple translation between numbers and byte sequences and encoding and decoding of varints.

name: gob
description: Package csv reads and writes comma-separated values (CSV) files.

name: hex
description: Package gob manages streams of gobs - binary values exchanged between an Encoder (transmitter) and a Decoder (receiver).

name: json
description: Package hex implements hexadecimal encoding and decoding.

name: pem
description: Package json implements encoding and decoding of JSON as defined in RFC 7159.

name: xml
description: Package pem implements the PEM data encoding, which originated in Privacy Enhanced Mail.

name: errors
description: Package xml implements a simple XML 1.0 parser that understands XML name spaces.

name: expvar
description: Package errors implements functions to manipulate errors.

name: flag
description: Package expvar provides a standardized interface to public variables, such as operation counters in servers.

name: fmt
description: Package flag implements command-line flag parsing.

name: go
description: Package fmt implements formatted I/O with functions analogous to C's printf and scanf.

name: build
description: Package ast declares the types used to represent syntax trees for Go packages.

name: constant
description: Package build gathers information about Go packages.

name: doc
description: Package constant implements Values representing untyped Go constants and their corresponding operations.

name: format
description: Package doc extracts source code documentation from a Go AST.

name: importer
description: Package format implements standard formatting of Go source.

name: parser
description: Package importer provides access to export data importers.

name: printer
description: Package parser implements a parser for Go source files.

name: scanner
description: Package printer implements printing of AST nodes.

name: token
description: Package scanner implements a scanner for Go source text.

name: types
description: Package token defines constants representing the lexical tokens of the Go programming language and basic operations on tokens (printing, predicates).

name: hash
description: Package types declares the data types and implements the algorithms for type-checking of Go packages.

name: adler32
description: Package hash provides interfaces for hash functions.

name: crc32
description: Package adler32 implements the Adler-32 checksum.

name: crc64
description: Package crc32 implements the 32-bit cyclic redundancy check, or CRC-32, checksum.

name: fnv
description: Package crc64 implements the 64-bit cyclic redundancy check, or CRC-64, checksum.

name: maphash
description: Package fnv implements FNV-1 and FNV-1a, non-cryptographic hash functions created by Glenn Fowler, Landon Curt Noll, and Phong Vo.

name: html
description: Package maphash provides hash functions on byte sequences.

name: template
description: Package html provides functions for escaping and unescaping HTML text.

name: image
description: Package template (html/template) implements data-driven templates for generating HTML output safe against code injection.

name: color
description: Package image implements a basic 2-D image library.

name: palette
description: Package color implements a basic color library.

name: draw
description: Package palette provides standard color palettes.

name: gif
description: Package draw provides image composition functions.

name: jpeg
description: Package gif implements a GIF image decoder and encoder.

name: png
description: Package jpeg implements a JPEG image decoder and encoder.

name: index
description: Package png implements a PNG image decoder and encoder.

name: io
description: Package suffixarray implements substring search in logarithmic time using an in-memory suffix array.

name: ioutil
description: Package io provides basic interfaces to I/O primitives.

name: log
description: Package ioutil implements some I/O utility functions.

name: syslog
description: Package log implements a simple logging package.

name: math
description: Package syslog provides a simple interface to the system log service.

name: big
description: Package math provides basic constants and mathematical functions.

name: bits
description: Package big implements arbitrary-precision arithmetic (big numbers).

name: cmplx
description: Package bits implements bit counting and manipulation functions for the predeclared unsigned integer types.

name: rand
description: Package cmplx provides basic constants and mathematical functions for complex numbers.

name: mime
description: Package rand implements pseudo-random number generators.

name: multipart
description: Package mime implements parts of the MIME spec.

name: quotedprintable
description: Package multipart implements MIME multipart parsing, as defined in RFC 2046.

name: net
description: Package quotedprintable implements quoted-printable encoding as specified by RFC 2045.

name: http
description: Package net provides a portable interface for network I/O, including TCP/IP, UDP, domain name resolution, and Unix domain sockets.

name: cgi
description: Package http provides HTTP client and server implementations.

name: cookiejar
description: Package cgi implements CGI (Common Gateway Interface) as specified in RFC 3875.

name: fcgi
description: Package cookiejar implements an in-memory RFC 6265-compliant http.CookieJar.

name: httptest
description: Package fcgi implements the FastCGI protocol.

name: httptrace
description: Package httptest provides utilities for HTTP testing.

name: httputil
description: Package httptrace provides mechanisms to trace the events within HTTP client requests.

name: pprof
description: Package httputil provides HTTP utility functions, complementing the more common ones in the net/http package.

name: mail
description: Package pprof serves via its HTTP server runtime profiling data in the format expected by the pprof visualization tool.

name: rpc
description: Package mail implements parsing of mail messages.

name: jsonrpc
description: Package rpc provides access to the exported methods of an object across a network or other I/O connection.

name: smtp
description: Package jsonrpc implements a JSON-RPC 1.0 ClientCodec and ServerCodec for the rpc package.

name: textproto
description: Package smtp implements the Simple Mail Transfer Protocol as defined in RFC 5321.

name: url
description: Package textproto implements generic support for text-based request/response protocols in the style of HTTP, NNTP, and SMTP.

name: os
description: Package url parses URLs and implements query escaping.

name: exec
description: Package os provides a platform-independent interface to operating system functionality.

name: signal
description: Package exec runs external commands.

name: user
description: Package signal implements access to incoming signals.

name: path
description: Package user allows user account lookups by name or id.

name: filepath
description: Package path implements utility routines for manipulating slash-separated paths.

name: plugin
description: Package filepath implements utility routines for manipulating filename paths in a way compatible with the target operating system-defined file paths.

name: reflect
description: Package plugin implements loading and symbol resolution of Go plugins.

name: regexp
description: Package reflect implements run-time reflection, allowing a program to manipulate objects with arbitrary types.

name: syntax
description: Package regexp implements regular expression search.

name: runtime
description: Package syntax parses regular expressions into parse trees and compiles parse trees into programs.

name: cgo
description: Package runtime contains operations that interact with Go's runtime system, such as functions to control goroutines.

name: debug
description: Package cgo contains runtime support for code generated by the cgo tool.

name: msan
description: Package debug contains facilities for programs to debug themselves while they are running.

name: race
description: Package pprof writes runtime profiling data in the format expected by the pprof visualization tool.

name: trace
description: Package race implements data race detection logic.

name: sort
description: Package trace contains facilities for programs to generate traces for the Go execution tracer.

name: strconv
description: Package sort provides primitives for sorting slices and user-defined collections.

name: strings
description: Package strconv implements conversions to and from string representations of basic data types.

name: sync
description: Package strings implements simple functions to manipulate UTF-8 encoded strings.

name: atomic
description: Package sync provides basic synchronization primitives such as mutual exclusion locks.

name: syscall
description: Package atomic provides low-level atomic memory primitives useful for implementing synchronization algorithms.

name: js
description: Package syscall contains an interface to the low-level operating system primitives.

name: testing
description: Package js gives access to the WebAssembly host environment when using the js/wasm architecture.

name: iotest
description: Package testing provides support for automated testing of Go packages.

name: quick
description: Package iotest implements Readers and Writers useful mainly for testing.

name: text
description: Package quick implements utility functions to help with black box testing.

name: tabwriter
description: Package scanner provides a scanner and tokenizer for UTF-8-encoded text.

name: template
description: Package tabwriter implements a write filter (tabwriter.Writer) that translates tabbed columns in input into properly aligned text.

name: parse
description: Package template implements data-driven templates for generating textual output.

name: time
description: Package parse builds parse trees for templates as defined by text/template and html/template.

name: unicode
description: Package time provides functionality for measuring and displaying time.

name: utf16
description: Package unicode provides data and functions to test some properties of Unicode code points.

name: utf8
description: Package utf16 implements encoding and decoding of UTF-16 sequences.

name: unsafe
description: Package utf8 implements functions and constants to support text encoded in UTF-8.
